<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="99" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="99">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Julius" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Capparaceae" genus="Capparis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Capparis trinervia subsp. var. var. chungiana" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="trinervia" subSpecies="var." variety="chungiana">Capparis trinervia var. chungiana</taxonomicName>
inhabits forest margins, gaps or pathways near to roadsides, but is not a common species. This species has not been relocated in Selangor and Pahang even though the localities and adjacent areas have been revisited. This species, however, has been found and recorded from a new locality in Negeri Sembilan during a botanical survey in 2010, but it could not be relocated from two recent visits in 2014 and 2019. Recent field observations to Negeri Sembilan also show forest clearing pathways near the species habitat. Therefore, this species is assessed as Near Threatened following the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" refId="B18" refString="IUCN, 2001. IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria.Version 3.1. 1st edn. IUCN Species Survival Commission, IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK." title="IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 3.1. 1 st edn. IUCN Species Survival Commission, IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK." year="2001">IUCN 2001</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" refId="B19" refString="IUCN, 2012. IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 3.1. 2nd edn. IUCN Species Survival Commission, IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK." title="IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 3.1. 2 nd edn. IUCN Species Survival Commission, IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK." year="2012">2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
